Citation.sTitle: Vapor-Liquid Equilibrium for the Carbon Dioxide + Hydrogen + Methanol Ternary System
Citation.sAbstract: Vapor-liquid equilibrium data for the ternary system carbon dioxide (CO2) + hydrogen (H2) + methanol (MeOH) were determined at temperatures between 278 K and 298 K and pressures between 20 bar and 200 bar. A dynamic technique with vapor and liquid recirculation and on-line gas chromatography was used in this study.
